results.name: Primes that can be obtained from other primes by interchanging the first and last digits. The source prime and the resulting prime are written consecutively.
comment: This sequence is different from A007500 and A069706. [From _Parthasarathy Nambi_, Aug 07 2010]
example: 389 is a prime and the prime 983 is obtained by interchanging the first and last digits.
results.author: _Parthasarathy Nambi_, Aug 06 2010
